{{Quote|If Guildmaster Cradossk demanded a sit-down with the heads of Lerrimore or Ayelix/Krongbing, they'd trip over their desks to greet him.|Arack Dostryt, in a chapter of the ''Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook''|<ref name="TBHC">''[[The Bounty Hunter Code: From the Files of Boba Fett]]''</ref>}}
'''Lerrimore Droids''' was a [[Droid/Legends|droid]] manufacturer which produced the [[KPR security droid/Legends|KPR servant droid]]<ref name="CCG" /> by [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]].<ref name="CCG date">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=2X-3KPR}} is concurrent to {{Film|IV}}, which is placed in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] by ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> Prior to the [[Bounty Hunters' Guild/Legends|Bounty Hunters' Guild]] [[Guild Master/Legends|Guildmaster]] [[Cradossk/Legends|Cradossk's]] [[Death/Legends|death]] in [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="Cradossk date">''[[The Mandalorian Armor]]'' establishes [[Cradossk/Legends|Cradossk's]] [[Death/Legends|death]] in the [[Battle of Circumtore]], dated to four [[Standard year/Legends|years]] before [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]] in ''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''.</ref> the guild owned stock in Lerrimore Droids, which sold KPR servant droids at a discount to Guild members. [[Arack Dostryt]], who was the guild's director of recruiting, noted in a chapter of the ''[[Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook]]'' that Lerrimore Droids was one of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] cornerstone corporations and that the organization's executive leadership would be eager to respond to Cradossk hypothetically demanding to see them.<ref name="TBHC" />

[[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]], Cradossk's son and himself an eventual [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]], later went on to annotate a ''Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook'' copy, asking why his [[Parent/Legends|father]] would want to meet organizations such as droid manufacturers.<ref name="TBHC" /> Lerrimore Droids shared its name<ref name="CCG" /> with [[Lerrimore Contracting Company]], a household goods manufacturer.<ref name="Arms site">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20021017web|text=''Arms & Equipment Guide'' Extras!}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Lerrimore Droids was created for the [[1995]] ''[[Premiere Limited]]'' set of the [[Decipher]] [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" />

